mation.%20Once%20confined%20to%20her%20home%2C%20she%20now%20travels%20to%20schools%20and%20community%20spaces%20to%20hold%20menstrual%20hygiene%20sessions.%20%E2%80%9CI%20go%20to%20schools%20just%20after%20my%20classes%20end.%20I%20ask%20the%20principal%20if%20I%20can%20speak%20to%20the%20girls%20for%20a%20few%20minutes%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20almost%20always%2C%20they%20say%20yes.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20each%20session%2C%20her%20confidence%20grows.%20So%20does%20her%20pride.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20morning%2C%20my%20husband%20asked%20me%20for%20Rs%201%2C000%2C%20and%20I%20told%20him%20%E2%80%94%20I%20can%20give%20you%20Rs%202%2C500%20also%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds%20with%20a%20smile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Don%E2%80%99t%20sit%20here%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20touch%20that%E2%80%99%3A%20Breaking%20the%20stigma%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20journey%20isn%E2%80%99t%20smooth%20for%20everyone.%20For%20many%20Kalyanis%2C%20stepping%20into%20the%20role%20of%20a%20menstrual%20health%20educator%20means%20pushing%20back%20against%20years%20of%20silence%E2%80%94and%20sometimes%2C%20direct%20resistance%20from%20their%20own%20families.%20Nidhi%2C%20the%20Kalyani%20network%20coordinator%2C%20recalls%20how%20even%20the%20idea%20of%20selling%20pads%20or%20talking%20openly%20about%20periods%20is%20difficult%20for%20some%20women%20to%20embrace.%20%E2%80%9CSelling%20pads%3F%20Talking%20about%20periods%3F%20For%20many%20husbands%20and%20elders%2C%20it%20was%20unacceptable%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20explains%20where%20that%20discomfort%20begins.%20%E2%80%9CFrom%20the%20time%20girls%20are%20small%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20told%3A%20%E2%80%98Don%E2%80%99t%20sit%20here%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98Don%E2%80%99t%20touch%20that.%E2%80%99%20Menstruation%20is%20made%20out%20to%20be%20something%20shameful%2C%20something%20unclean.%E2%80%9D%20These%20beliefs%20aren%E2%80%99t%20confined%20to%20any%20one%20comm